comments.body:
Given how many applications just hang if aardvark keeps the fd open we should come up with a different way to launch aardvark.

I think it would help if we implement the actual daemon part in aardvark-dns and not netavark. So netavark launches aardvark  with stdout/err attached and aardvark startup code could write errors to stderr and the users would see them. Aardvark should fork itself and set the stdin/out/err to /dev/null once it is ready to serve dns the parent aardvark process should exit. Netavark should wait until the aardvark parent exists. This would allow us to get proper error output in case of errors and would remove the current race since netavark returns before aardvark is actually ready.

@baude @mheon @flouthoc WDYT?
